Can you explain the concept of "mindful eating" and how it can help with weight management?

Mindful eating is the practice of paying attention to the experience of eating and drinking, including the taste, texture, and smell of food. It involves being present in the moment and not getting distracted by thoughts or emotions. Mindful eating can help with weight management by reducing overeating and increasing feelings of fullness. When you are mindful of your food, you are more likely to eat less and enjoy your meals more. Additionally, mindful eating can help you recognize when you are overeating and stop eating when you feel full.
